Role of Piezo channels in mechanotransduction {#sec1-2045894018767393}
=============================================

Mechanotransduction is defined as a process by which cells convert a mechanical stimulus into electrical or chemical signals which allow the cells to adapt to mechanical changes in the *milieu*. Mechanosensitive channels are transmembrane proteins that respond to mechanical stress over a wide dynamic range of external mechanical stimuli.

