1. Background {#sec16165}
=============

Structural heart disease and heart failure (HF) can lead to electrical and structural remodeling of the atria ([@A10332R1]). As a result of fibrosis, change in atrial size, increased anisotropy, cellular uncoupling and dispersion of refractoriness alteration in atrial conduction may occur ([@A10332R1], [@A10332R2]). Atrial fibrosis is a hallmark of structural remodeling that contributes to the AF substrate and hence cerebral ischemic events and an increased risk of death ([@A10332R3]-[@A10332R5]).

